Common Ubuntu Commands:

ls -- Lists the files and folders in the current directory.

cd [folder] -- moves you into another folder (changes directory).

cd .. -- Backs out of current folder

cd ~ -- Go to your home folder

pwd -- shows the current directory you are in.

Control + C  -- Stop running program and bring cmd line back 

sudo halt -- safely shut down pi

cp -- copies a file from one location to another on the same system.

nano FILENAME.py - To open and modify the file, then save( CTRL + O), then exit(CTRL + X)

python3 -- runs a Python script.

exit -- ends the session and returns to local computer


In command prompt:
scp -- securely copies files between computers(Such as raspberry pi and laptop)
Example:
scp USERNAME@(Current IP address):/home/USERNAME/(folder)(Filename) C:\Users\Yourname\Desktop\


Remote Login:
ssh USERNAME@cs350lab.local -- Connects to Raspberry Pi remotely
